frameDefinitions: A Law regulates activities or states of affairs within a Jurisdiction, dictating what Required states should be the case and what Forbidden states should not.
This frame contains items which, when manipulated, alter the function of some device, internal or external.
A Controlling_entity has control of a Dependent_entity, Dependent_situation, or Dependent_variable.
An Agent acts to ensure that a Rule (often a constraint on behavior) is being followed.
A Controlling_entity, Controlling_situation, or Controlling_variable control a Dependent_entity, Dependent_situation, or Dependent_variable.
These are words referring to control by a Leader over a particular entity  or group (the Governed) or an Activity.
frameExamples: The new <t>act</t> banning smoking in public will pass soon.
This <t>button</t> makes the radio turn on.
She was in <t>control</t> of the empire within two days.
Why don't we <t>enforce</t> the 20000 gun laws currently on the books across the nation?
Sebek em hat was a <t>Leader</t> of Priests. ca. 1780 BC
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the rule designed to guide activity, deprecating some types of activity and/or requiring other types of activity. This role is incorporated into each LU in this frame.
The state-of-affairs which is disallowed by the <fen>Law</fen>.
A state-of-affairs which the <fen>Law</fen> declares must be maintained.
This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>. This is often an incorporated FE.
A thing or person whose behavior controls a <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>, <fen>Dependent_situation</fen>, or <fen>Dependent_variable</fen>.
An entity, usually a thing, that is influenced in its behavior by a <fen>Controlling_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the controlling occurs.
The location at which the controlling occurs.
The <fen>Rule</fen> is the set of constrants on behavior that the <fen>Agent</fen> implements (i.e., forces others to obey or face consequences).
The <fen>Agent</fen>, often an institution, governmental organization, or arm thereof, puts into effect (i.e., enforces) a <fen>Rule</fen>.
This role describes the medium through which the rule was enforced.  It may occur in the same syntactic position as the Agent.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the Agent enforces the <fen>Rule</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Rule</fen> is or is not enforced.
A thing or person whose behavior controls a <fen>Dependent_entity</fen>, <fen>Dependent_situation</fen>, or <fen>Dependent_variable</fen>.
An entity, usually a thing, that is influenced in its behavior by a <fen>Controlling_entity</fen> or an <fen>Controlling_situation</fen>.
The <fex name='tim'>Time</fex> at which the controlling occurs.
The location at which the controlling occurs.

The <fen>Leader</fen> is the one who has the role of leading.  With verbs, and with predicate nominals linking an individual to a <fen>Role</fen>, the <fen>Leader</fen> is usually the External Argument:

The role played by the <fen>Leader</fen> in a given situation, often an official title; incorporated in most noun LUsin this frame. When expressed separately from the target, <fen>Role</fen> usually occurs in a PP Complement headed by <ment>as</ment>.
The entity whose actions or beliefs the <fen>Leader</fen> directs in the context of a joint activity or movement.  This entity can be a political body, a person, or a group of people.
The <fen>Leader</fen> directs the <fen>Activity</fen>.
<fen>Time</fen> refers to the point in time that the leadership took place.
The locale from which the <fen>Leader</fen> leads the <fen>Governed</fen> or the <fen>Activity</fen>.
listRoleExamples: I think we need a law <fex>against all firearms within city limits</fex>.
The law <fex>that all minors must be accompanied by an adult</fex> is a laughingstock.
Employers should strictly enforce <fex>a prohibition against use of any substance that may affect a worker's physical or mental ability</fex>.
Can <fex>a landlord</fex> enforce rules upon tenants?
The rules will be enforced <fex>by a new computer system that tracks people's movements</fex>.
That particular regulation was only enforced <fex>in 1920</fex>.
For this reason they enforced the settlement system <fex>in America</fex> just as strictly as in Germany.
The general led his troops into battle <fex>on June 22, 1883</fex>.
He ruled the west <fex>from his palace in Milan</fex>.
